{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"308d9a3f-896f-4bfd-8911-0823e4183ebf","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` with the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThis will:\n- **`dotnet watch test`** — re-run tests automatically on file save (hot reload)\n- **`--filter \"FullyQualifiedName~...\"`** — run only tests whose name contains that string\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so you don't need the full namespace. You can also filter by just the method name:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"Name=ProcessPayment_NegativeAmount_ThrowsException\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fc7d92a1-8e33-4844-9bac-87d26c43ac8d","outputTokens":165,"requestId":"A804:1618E9:26B1226:292E6D6:6A04943A"},"id":"17b6becf-dac8-4817-917f-dd84beeefa98","timestamp":"2026-05-13T15:09:52.106Z","parentId":"56f51b89-2a83-428e-b752-b4e08c1239e8"}
